<p><b>Cannonballs</b> are <a href="/w/Ammunition" class="mw-redirect" title="Ammunition">ammunition</a> used in the <a href="/w/Dwarf_multicannon" title="Dwarf multicannon">Dwarf multicannon</a>. </p><p><a href="/w/Granite_dust" title="Granite dust">Granite dust</a> can be used on cannonballs to create <a href="/w/Granite_cannonball" title="Granite cannonball">granite cannonballs</a>, which have a higher max hit. This requires level 50 Smithing and yields no experience.
</p>

<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Making_them">Making them</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/Cannonball?section=3&amp;veaction=edit" class="mw-editsection-visualeditor" title="Edit section: Making them">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-divider"> | </span><a href="/w/Cannonball?action=edit&amp;section=3" title="Edit section: Making them">edit source</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>
<div class="thumb tright"><div class="thumbinner" style="width:308px;"><a href="/w/File:Cannonball_Smithing.gif" class="image"><img alt="" src="/images/8/81/Cannonball_Smithing.gif?da0b2" width="306" height="216" class="thumbimage" data-file-width="306" data-file-height="216" /></a>  <div class="thumbcaption">A player smithing cannonballs.</div></div></div>
<p>Making cannonballs is a popular method for players to train Smithing and profit without requiring much input or attention. A full inventory takes 159.6 seconds to process. Optimal speeds yield nearly 14,000 Smithing experience per hour from converting a total of 540 steel bars into 2,160 cannonballs when not using the <a href="/w/Prifddinas" title="Prifddinas">Prifddinas</a> furnace. Using a furnace closer to a bank will increase efficiency.
</p><p>Players can also smelt one <a href="/w/Iron_ore" title="Iron ore">iron ore</a> and two <a href="/w/Coal" title="Coal">coal</a> to make the steel bars and then use them to make cannonballs without returning to a bank, but it is very slow.
